article.headline: UNLV 68, San Diego State 61
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Wink Adams scored a game-high 20 points to lead UNLV past San Diego State 68-61 in a Mountain West Conference game Tuesday night. Adams shot 6-of-8 from the field, including 4-of-4 from 3-point range, in the second half for UNLV (17-4, 4-2 Mountain West Conference). Gaston Essengue had 10 points and five rebounds while Joel Anthony added nine points and eight rebounds for the Rebels. Brandon Heath led San Diego State (13-7, 2-4) with 20 points. Lorrenzo Wade scored 11 points and 11 rebounds and Jerome Habel added nine points and seven rebounds for the Aztecs. After San Diego State led 25-23 at the break, the lead changed seven times. UNLV eventually took the lead for good on Marcus Lawrence's 3-pointer with 14:05 left, 36-34. That was the start of a 17-3 run, giving the Rebels their largest lead at 50-37. The Aztecs cut the lead to 59-55 with 2:03 left, but came no closer. The Rebels shot 23-of-64, or 36 percent, from the field. The Aztecs shot 27-of-60, or 45 percent. The Rebels were without senior guard Kevin Kruger, their number three leading scorer. Kruger suffered a deep thigh bruise at Wyoming Jan. 10 and now has missed UNLV's last three games.
